==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[ορφανός]]''' (''orfanos'') "without parents, fatherless".
===Noun===
'''orphan''' ([[orphans]])
# a [[person]] one or both of whose [[parent]]s have died, especially a minor
# [[child]] without [[living]] [[parent]]s
# a [[young]] [[animal]] with no [[mother]]
#(''typography'') a [[single]] [[line]] of [[type]], beginning a [[paragraph]], at the [[bottom]] of a [[column]] or [[page]]
#(''computing'') a computer image without an associated an associated file

